## Hybrid AI rerank (<=20s target)

- Flow (frontend `/api/recommendations`):
  - Deprecated; frontend should call backend directly.
  - Backend endpoints:
    - `POST /api/recommend/` (baseline matcher)
    - `POST /api/recommend/rerank/` (baseline + OpenAI; fallback to baseline on timeout/error)
- Env/config:
  - `OPENAI_MODEL` (default `gpt-5-nano`)
  - `OPENAI_API_KEY`
  - `OPENAI_RERANK_TOP_K` (default `30`)
  - `OPENAI_RERANK_TIMEOUT_MS` (default `9000`)
- Response shape:
  - `{ rankings: [{ id, matchPercentage, reasons[] }], fallback: boolean, elapsedMs }`
- Notes:
  - IDs must match backend matcher output; reasons present only when AI rerank succeeds.
  - Keep total SLA under ~20s by bounding backend (~<1s) + OpenAI (~<9s) + overhead.
